modules.description: This module processes strings encoded in WTF-8, a superset of UTF-8 that accepts invalid Unicode encodings. It provides `fold_wtf_8` to iterate over code points, handling malformed sequences, and `add_wtf_8` to append code points to a buffer. It works directly with `string` input and operates on `codepoint` values, which represent either valid Unicode code points or malformed sequences. Use this module when parsing or constructing strings that may contain invalid UTF-8, such as when handling user input with unknown encoding.
